        Company name

        This display's your company name. If at any time, you need to refresh the current section or go to the business central home page, just click this link.

        To manage information about your company, click on Tell Me and type in "Company Information".

        To create a new company, click on Settings and Select "My Settings". There you can view basic settings about your company. Then, click on the beside your company name and finally, click on "New" on the next page that appears.

        Customers

        Click this to quickly create, edit and manage customers.

        Click this to quickly create, edit and manage vendors.

        To migrate vendors from another source, click on Tell Me and type in "Data Migration".

        Items

        Click this to quickly create, edit and manage items in your company.

        Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central is designed with a simple approach to items. An item can basically be anything, they can be inventory, non-inventory and even services. An item is registered with an ID number, description, the quantity at hand, and even an image if one is available. Items should be registered with enough information to maintain a well structured inventory.

        Actions

        Actions are a collection of links to key features in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central. Business Central is designed this way to make it easier and faster for you to access key features and services.

        Create sales quotes, invoices, purchase orders, payments and reports right from the home screen.

        The Activities Section

        The Activities section is designed to provide you with statical information regarding your company.

        Clicking on an information block would take you directly to a page where you can view or manage the information it contains.

        Cues in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central are color indications that indicate how favourable a certain piece of information is.

        For example:

        Overdue Sales Invoice
        Amount
        $63,890
        Favorable
        See more
        Overdue Purch. Invoice
        Amount
        $49,422
        Unfavorable
        See more

        The overdue sales invoice amount on the left is marked with a green cue indicator, this shows that it is favourable and acceptable. The overdue purchase invoice on the other hand is unfavourable and is marked red.

        Cues can be customized to make indications based on what the current statistical information is at a certain time.

        To customize cue indicators, click on Activities and select "Set Up Cue Indicators".

        Business Insights

        Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central provides charts and graphs to demonstrate statistical data in your company.

        Each chunck of the chart in the current home page represents customers in a demo company on Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central. From the chart, it would be right to conclude that School of Fine Art is the top customer in the company (this can also be seen in the headline), followed by Adatum Corporation, and then Relecloud, Apline Ski House and finally, Trey Research. Hovering your mouse over charts in Business Central, will provide more information on the values and their sources.

        The visual representation and the representation of this data can be changed to provide more precise information.

        To change the representation type, click on Business Assistance and select from the list. To view a demonstration on this, click here, be sure to carefully watch as it is a small part of the video.

        Trial Balanace

        This is a quick overview of your company's financial performance.

        The table is comprised of three columns, the first contains a description of the item to be evaluated, the next two columns contain values of the item based on a certain date.

        Based on the table in the home screen, it is possible to denote that the total revenue of CRONUS USA, Inc. was $45, 932.75 within the 1st to 31st of March 2018 and that it fell to $1,188.62 within the 1st to 31st of April, 2018.

        The values on the table are colored to indicate when a value is below zero. According to the table, CRONUS USA, Inc. has had a low Operating Margin % which has only gone lower for more than 2 months. Getting insights like this makes detecting and solving business problems easier and faster.

          Finance

          Click this to take a look at and update standard configuration of basic financial processes. A few of these processes include:

          Managing Receivables:
          Apply incoming payments, reconcile bank accounts during payment application, and collect outstanding balances.

          Managing Payables:
          Make payments, apply outgoing payments, and work with checks.

          Invoicing Prepayments:
          Make your customers submit payment before you ship to them, or submit payment to your vendors before they ship to you.

          Managing Bank Accounts:
          Reconcile bank accounts and transfer funds between bank accounts.

          Accounting for Costs:
          Analyze the costs of running your business by allocating actual and budgeted costs of operations, departments, products, and projects to cost centers.

          Managing Inventory Costs:
          Manage inventory and manufacturing costs, report costs, and reconcile costs with the general ledger.

          Working with Dimensions:
          Add dimensions for richer business intelligence.

          Update Currency Exchange Rates:
          Learn how to use additional currencies and update currency exchange rates automatically.

          Cash Management

          Click this to collect and make payments, prepare statements and reconcile bank accounts.

          Cash Flow Forecasts:
          Helps estimate the amount of money that'll move in and out of your business.

          Cash Receipt Journals:
          keep track of the sales of items when cash is received, by crediting sales and debiting cash and transactions related to receipts.

          Payment Journals:
          A journal that allows you to record all cash payments - that is, all transactions during which you spend funds.

          Bank Accounts:
          keep track of your banking transactions.

          Bank Acc. Statements:
          A summary of financial transactions which have occurred over a given period on a bank account

          Payment Terms:
          Set the conditions under which a seller will complete a sale.

          Sales

          Click this to sell products and register new customers, create special orders and make sales quotes.

          Register New Customers:
          Create a customer card for each customer that you sell to.

          Make Sales Quotes:
          Create a sales quote where you offer products on negotiable terms before converting the quote to a sales invoice.

          Sell Products:
          Process a sales order that involves partial shipping or drop shipment.

          Make Drop Shipments:
          Link a sales order to a purchase order to sell a drop-shipment item that will be delivered directly from your vendor to your customer.

          Create Special Orders:
          Have a catalog item shipped from a vendor to your warehouse so that you can ship the item on to your customer.

          Process Sales Returns or Cancellations:
          Create a sales credit memo to revert a specific posted sales invoice to reflect which products the customer returns and which payment amount you will refund.

          Purchasing

          Click this to create a purchase invoice or purchase order to record the cost of purchases and to track accounts payable.

          Record Purchases:
          Create a purchase invoice to record your agreement with a vendor to purchase products on certain delivery and payment terms.

          Request Quotes:
          Create a purchase quote to reflect a request for quote from your vendor, which you can later convert to a purchase order.

          Purchase Items for a Sale:
          Create a purchase invoice for all or selected lines on a sales invoice.

          Correct or Cancel Unpaid Sales Invoices:
          Perform an action on an unpaid posted purchase invoice to automatically create a credit memo and either cancel the purchase invoice or recreate it so you can make corrections.

          Process Purchase Returns or Cancellations:
          Create a purchase credit memo to revert a specific posted purchase invoice to reflect which products you are returning to the vendor and which payment amount you will collect.

          Combine Receipts on a Single Invoice:
          Prepare to invoice multiple receipts from the same vendor once by combining the receipts on one invoice.

          Receive and Convert Electronic Documents:
          Convert, for example, electronic invoices from your vendors to purchase invoices inside Business Central.

          Approvals

          Click here to create a request to approve card and a workflow card.

          Self Service

          Click here to create time sheets and set user tasks.

          Setup & Extensions

          Click this to:

          Create and setup a new customer card.

          Create a new vendor template to add a new vendor.

          Create a new item card to add a new item amongst other things.

          Integrate your bank account into business central.

          Add, manage or delete a general ledger account in the charts of accounts page.

          To migrate to a setup or extension from another source, click on Tell Me and type in the setup or extension name.

          Intelligent Cloud Insights

          Click this to view intelligent cloud insights.

          As a user of Business Central online, you have full access to scenarios that are based on the intelligent cloud, such as editing data in Excel and pushing changes back to Business Central, or when you view your data in Power BI. However, while Business Central is a cloud-first service, also those customers who need to run their workloads fully on-premises or on the intelligent edge connected to the cloud can do so.

          To migrate to intelligent cloud insights from another source, click on Tell Me and type in "Intelligent Cloud Insights".
